Class TimingEdge

  • Object
    • org.jgrapht.graph.DefaultEdge
      • com.xilinx.rapidwright.timing.TimingEdge
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable

    public class TimingEdge
extends org.jgrapht.graph.DefaultEdge
    Edges within a TimingGraph that encapsulate logic delays, net delays, and debug information.

                  TimingVertex srcPort,

                  EDIFNet edifNet,
                  Net net)
        Constructs a TimingEdge with the expected information for the TimingGraph.
        Parameters:
        timingGraph - TimingGraph object where this edge will belong.
        srcPort - First vertex as a TimingVertex.
        dstPort - Second vertex as a TimingVertex.
        edifNet - Logical EDIFNet representing this edge. In some cases this is set to null.
        net - Physical "Net" representing this edge.
